  <Notes>
    <Note Caller="1" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References/>
      <Content>It is possible that εὔχομαι[a] and προσεύχομαι differ somewhat in the extent to which focus is upon the person to whom the prayer is addressed, but this cannot be determined from NT usage.</Content>
    </Note>
    <Note Caller="2" LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="" LastEditedBy="">
      <References>
        <Reference>04500900300002</Reference>
      </References>
      <Content>It is possible, but not very probable, that εὔχομαι in {S:04500900300002} could mean ‘to pray’ (see {D:33.178}).</Content>
    </Note>
